egory:West Bromwich Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Oxford United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Shrewsbury Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Walsall F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:English people of Welsh descent]]\n[[Category:Wales under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Leeds United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wales international footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Tyler Roberts\n| image = TylerRoberts2019.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Tyler D'Whyte Roberts<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/-/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/january-2018.ashx |title=List of Players under Written Contract Registered Between 01/01/2018 and 31/01/2018 |publisher=The Football Association |page=8 |format=PDF |access-date=17 June 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1999|01|12|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Gloucester]], England\n| height = {{convert|1.80|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/tyler-roberts/ |title=Tyler Roberts |website=worldfootball.net |language=en |access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]], [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]], [[attacking midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| clubnumber = 11\n| youthyears1 = 2006\u20132016\n| youthclubs1 = [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]\n| years1 = 2016\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]\n| caps1 = 1\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2016\u20132017\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]] (loan)\n| caps2 = 14\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2017\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] (loan)\n| caps3 = 13\n| goals3 = 4\n| years4 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 17\n| goals4 = 5\n| years5 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| caps5 = 41\n| goals5 = 6\n| nationalyears1 = 2015\u20132016\n| nationalteam1 = [[Wales national under-17 football team|Wales U17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 10\n| nationalgoals1 = 3\n| nationalyears2 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam2 = [[Wales national under-19 football team|Wales U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 2\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2017\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Wales national under-20 football team|Wales U20]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 2\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2017\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Wales national under-21 football team|Wales U21]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 5\n| nationalgoals4 = 1\n| nationalyears5 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam5 = [[Wales national football team|Wales]]\n| nationalcaps5 = 7\n| nationalgoals5 = 0\n| club-update = 06:09, 1 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 22:21, 13 October 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Tyler D'Whyte Roberts''' (born 12 January 1999) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] and the [[Wales national football team]].\n\nHe is an academy graduate of [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] and made his professional debut for the club in May 2016. [[Loan (sports)|Loan]] spells in [[League One]] with [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]], [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] and [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] followed before he joined [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds]] in January 2018. He also made his senior Wales debut in 2018, having previously represented the nation at various youth levels.\n\nA versatile forward, he can play as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]], [[Winger (association football)|winger]] or as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\n===West Bromwich Albion===\n====Early career====\nHaving spotted him playing for junior side Tredworth Tigers at a Gloucester Festival, [[West Bromwich Albion|West Brom]] decided to sign Roberts for their academy when he was just seven years old.<ref name=\"BBC1\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/35312778 |title=Tyler Roberts: West Brom give teenager professional contract |date=14 January 2016 |access-date=25 April 2016 |publisher=BBC}}</ref> Having then gone on to represent the club at age group level, Roberts was named on West Brom's bench for the first time on the final day of the [[2014\u201315 West Bromwich Albion F.C. season|2014\u201315 season]] against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]. However, he did not make it on to the pitch.<ref name=\"WO\">{{Cite news |last=Southcombe |first=Matthew (26 May 2015) |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/who-tyler-roberts-meet-16-year-old-9330298 |title=Who is Tyler Roberts? Meet the 16-year-old West Brom sensation who has been called up to train with Wales |work=Wales Online |access-date=25 April 2016}}</ref> Following Roberts' inclusion in the squad, he was listed by ''[[Match of the Day]]'' magazine as one of the 20 wonder-kids to look out for in 2016.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Suart |first=Paul (7 January 2016) |url=http://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/west-broms-tyler-roberts-more-10702084 |title=West Brom's Tyler Roberts: More recognition for Albion's next big prospect |work=Birmingham Mail |access-date=16 May 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 January 2016, just two days after his 17th birthday, Roberts signed his first professional contract with West Brom, putting pen to paper on a {{frac|2|1|2}}-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.wba.co.uk/news/article/albion-west-brom-tyler-roberts-professional-contract-2900604.aspx |title=Talented Roberts pens pro deal |date=14 January 2016 |access-date=25 April 2016 |publisher=West Bromwich Albion}}</ref> He made his [[Premier League]] debut for the club on the final day of the [[2015\u201316 West Bromwich Albion F.C. season|2015\u201316 season]] in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], coming on as a second-half [[substitute (association football)|substitute]] for fellow Albion academy graduate [[Jonathan Leko]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=White |first=Jim (15 May 2016) |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/05/15/west-brom-1-liverpool-1-forgettable-draw-leaves-liverpools-europ/ |title=West Brom 1 Liverpool 1: Forgettable draw leaves Liverpool's European hopes on the brink |access-date=15 May 2016 |website=Telegraph}}</ref> Shortly after coming on, Roberts was [[Fouls and misconduct (association football)#yellow card (caution)|booked]] for a rash challenge on Liverpool captain [[Jordan Henderson]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/west-bromwich-albion-fc/2016/05/15/west-brom-1-liverpool-1-report/ |title=West Brom 1 Liverpool 1 \u2013 Report and pictures |date=15 May 2016 |access-date=15 May 2016 |website=Albion Express & Star}}</ref> Upon making his debut, Roberts became only the second player born in 1999 to play in the Premier League, following on from teammate Leko who had done so the month before.\n\n====2016\u201317 season: Loans to Oxford United and Shrewsbury Town====\nOn 28 July 2016, Roberts joined [[League One]] side [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]] on a six-month [[loan (sports)|loan]] deal until January 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.oufc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/oxford-united-west-brom-roberts-3211933.aspx |title=West Brom youngster joins the U's |date=28 July 2016 |publisher=Oxford United |access-date=28 July 2016}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on the opening day of the [[2016\u201317 Oxford United F.C. season|2016\u201317 season]], coming off the bench for [[Chris Maguire]] in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/chesterfield-fc/oxford-united-1-chesterfield-1-ched-evans-cracker-earns-spireites-a-point-1-8054893 |title=Oxford United 1 Chesterfield 1: Ched Evans cracker earns Spireites a point |date=6 August 2016 |access-date=7 August 2016 |website=The Star}}</ref> His [[Football League Cup|League Cup]] debut came the following week when he entered the field of play as an [[Overtime (sports)|extra-time]] [[substitute (association football)|substitute]] in Oxford's 1\u20130 win over [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sportskeeda.com/live-football-score/birmingham-city-vs-oxford-united-capital-one-cup-2016-17 |title=Birmingham City vs Oxford United Live Score and Commentary, Capital One Cup 2016\u201317 |date=9 August 2016 |access-date=10 August 2016 |website=Sportskeeda}}</ref> He then scored his first goal for the club, and the first professional goal of his career, in a 4\u20132 victory over [[League Two]] club [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]] in the [[2016\u201317 EFL Trophy]] on 30 August.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pritchard |first=David |url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/sport/oxfordunited/14713138.Small_Checkatrade_Trophy_gate_at_Oxford_United_cannot_take_gloss_off_Tyler_Roberts_s_first_professional_goal/ |title=Small Checkatrade Trophy gate at Oxford United cannot take gloss off Tyler Roberts's first professional goal |date=30 August 2016 |work=Oxford Mail |access-date=31 August 2016}}</ref> On 5 November, Roberts made his [[FA Cup]] debut and scored in a 5\u20130 win over [[Merstham F.C.|Merstham]] of the [[Isthmian League]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Amofa |first=Richard |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/11/05/merstham-0-oxford-united-5-clinical-visitors-display-class-on-an/ |title=Merstham 0 Oxford United 5: Clinical visitors display class on and off the pitch |date=5 November 2016 |access-date=6 November 2016 |website=Telegraph}}</ref> A month later, on 6 December, he scored the winning penalty in a shootout against [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]], after a 1\u20131 draw in the second round of the EFL Trophy.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pritchard |first=David |url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/sport/oxfordunited/14950749.Tyler_Roberts_holds_his_nerve_as_Oxford_United_make_it_third_time_lucky_with_shoot_out_win_over_Southend/ |title=Tyler Roberts holds his nerve as Oxford United make it third time lucky with shoot-out win over Southend |date=7 December 2016 |work=Oxford Mail |access-date=7 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nLater that month, Oxford [[Manager (association football)|manager]] [[Michael Appleton]] lodged a request to West Brom to extend Roberts' loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pritchard |first=David |url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/sport/14953921.Oxford_United_make_request_to_West_Bromwich_Albion_for_Tyler_Roberts_loan_extension/ |title=Oxford United make request to West Bromwich Albion for Tyler Roberts loan extension |date=8 December 2016 |access-date=13 December 2016 |website=Oxford Mail}}</ref> However, on 17 January 2017, Roberts  joined fellow League One side [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38651116 |title=Tyler Roberts: Shrewsbury Town sign West Bromwich Albion striker on loan |date=17 January 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=17 January 2017}}</ref> He made his debut for the club four days later, starting in a 1\u20130 league win over [[Oldham Athletic F.C.|Oldham Athletic]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.shropshirestar.com/sport/shrewsbury-town-fc/2017/01/21/shrewsbury-town-1-oldham-0-report/ |title=Shrewsbury Town 1 Oldham 0 - Report and pictures |date=21 January 2017 |website=Shropshire Star |access-date=22 January 2017}}</ref> Roberts scored his first goal for the club, and his first in league football, on 4 February when he netted the opener in a 2\u20131 win over [[Bury F.C.|Bury]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.shropshirestar.com/sport/shrewsbury-town-fc/2017/02/04/paul-hurst-hails-star-shrewsbury-town-striker-tyler-roberts-in-win-over-bury/ |title=Paul Hurst hails star Shrewsbury Town striker Tyler Roberts in win over Bury |date=4 February 2017 |website=Shropshire Star |access-date=5 February 2017}}</ref> On 4 April, Roberts suffered a hamstring injury in a 2\u20131 defeat to [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] that saw his stint at Shrewsbury come to an end.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.shropshirestar.com/sport/shrewsbury-town-fc/2017/04/21/shrewsbury-town-may-call-on-injured-tyler-roberts/ |title=Shrewsbury Town may call on injured Tyler Roberts |date=21 April 2017 |website=Shropshire Star |access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> He ended the campaign with four goals and two [[Assist (football)|assists]] for the club as they narrowly avoided relegation.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.shropshirestar.com/sport/football/shrewsbury-town-fc/2017/05/19/tyler-roberts-will-always-hold-shrewsbury-town-in-his-heart/ |title=Tyler Roberts will always hold Shrewsbury Town in his heart |date=19 May 2017 |website=Shropshire Star |access-date=23 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n====2017\u201318 season: Loan to Walsall====\nOn 25 August 2017, Roberts left West Brom on loan once again, joining League One side [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] for the season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41054998 |title=Tyler Roberts: Walsall sign West Bromwich Albion forward on loan |date=25 August 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=27 August 2017}}</ref> The following day, he scored one goal and [[Assist (football)|assisted]] another on debut against [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]], helping Walsall come from 3\u20130 down to earn a 3\u20133 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40983705 |title=Walsall 3\u20133 Bradford |date=26 August 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=27 August 2017}}</ref> He went on to score five goals in 17 appearances before being recalled by West Brom at the half-way mark of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/tyler-roberts-contract-west-brom-14219390 |title=Revealed: The latest on Tyler Roberts' West Brom future amid Leeds and Rangers links |last=Suart |first=Paul |date=30 January 2018 |website=Birmingham Mail |access-date=30 January 2018}}</ref> Upon completing his loan spell at [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]], Roberts was linked with a [[Bosman ruling|Bosman]] move to [[Serie A]] side [[AC Milan]] who had been scouting the player.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/soccer-transfers/story/3360606/ac-milansampdoria-and-torino-track-west-brom-striker-tyler-roberts |title=AC Milan, Sampdoria and Torino track West Brom striker Tyler Roberts |date=26 January 2018 |website=ESPN Sport |access-date=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Leeds United===\nRoberts' return to West Brom was short-lived, however, as the arrival of [[Daniel Sturridge]] on loan from Liverpool limited his first team chances further. As a result, on the final day of the January transfer market, he signed for [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side, [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] on a four-and-a-half-year deal for an undisclosed fee believed to be around an initial \u00a32.5 million potentially rising to \u00a34 million depending on clauses.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/22954/leeds-complete-tyler-roberts-transfer |title=Leeds Complete Tyler Roberts Transfer |access-date=31 January 2018 |publisher=Leeds United FC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11715/11230548/leeds-sign-tyler-roberts-from-west-brom-on-three-and-a-half-year-deal |title=Leeds sign Tyler Roberts from West Brom on three-and-a-half-year deal |access-date=31 January 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/leeds-united-summer-returns-likely-for-injured-whites-pair-1-9094079 |title=Leeds United: Summer returns likely for injured Whites pair |work=Yorkshire Evening Post |access-date=3 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nHaving recovered from a minor knock which he arrived at the club with, Roberts looked set to make his debut in the middle of February. However, on 14 February, new club manager [[Paul Heckingbottom]] revealed that he had cracked his shin bone upon his return in training and would be ruled out for several weeks.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/tyler-roberts-set-first-leeds-14282787 |title=Tyler Roberts set for first Leeds United start since signing from West Brom |last=Wollaston |first=Steve |date=13 February 2018 |website=Birmingham Mail |access-date=28 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/23015/tyler-roberts-picks-up-injury |title=Tyler Roberts Picks up Injury |access-date=14 February 2018 |publisher=Leeds United}}</ref> He ultimately missed the remainder of the season through the injury.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Urquhart |first=Joe |url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/paul-heckingbottom-reveals-what-tyler-roberts-will-bring-to-leeds-united-1-9151641 |title=Paul Heckingbottom reveals what Tyler Roberts will bring to Leeds United |date=5 May 2018 |work=Yorkshire Evening Post |access-date=18 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter spending several months on the sidelines, Roberts made his unofficial debut as a second-half substitute during a pre-season friendly against [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/southend |title=Southend United Vs Leeds United |date=22 July 2018 |access-date=22 July 2018 |publisher=Leeds United}}</ref> His full debut followed on 14 August when started for Leeds in an [[EFL Cup]] fixture against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/match |title=Leeds United vs Bolton |date=14 August 2018 |access-date=14 August 2018 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814232818/https://www.leedsunited.com/match |archive-date=14 August 2018 |publisher=Leeds United}}</ref> The following month, he made his league debut in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] and scored his first goals for the club three days later, scoring a brace in a 3\u20130 victory over [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45456100 |title=Leeds stay unbeaten with Millwall Draw |date=15 September 2018 |work=BBC Sport |access-date=15 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45479784 |title=Leeds Cruise Past Preston to stay top |date=18 September 2018 |work=BBC Sport |access-date=18 September 2018}}</ref> On 1 March he assisted [[Patrick Bamford]] twice in a 4\u20130 victory over former club [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]], with Roberts receiving the man of the match award playing in an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] position.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/live/football/47379196 |title=Relive Leeds' 4-0 win over West Brom |date=2019-02-27 |access-date=2019-03-01}}</ref>\n\nHe was one of three players nominated for the clubs end of season awards for Young Player Of The Season alongside [[Jamie Shackleton]] and [[Jack Clarke (footballer, born 2000)|Jack Clarke]], but lost out on the award on 28 April, with Clarke winning the award for Young Player Of The Season at the clubs annual ceremony.<ref name=\"Awards\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/24912/player-of-the-year-2019-winners |title=PLAYER OF THE YEAR 2019 WINNERS |date=28 April 2018 |publisher=Leeds United F.C |access-date=15 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nRoberts played 32 games scoring 3 goals in all competitions, after Leeds finished the regular season in third place after dropping out of the automatic promotion places with 3 games left after a defeat to 10 man [[Wigan Athletic]] on 19 April,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47904094 |title=Leeds 1 Wigan 2 |date=19 April 2019 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=15 May 2019}}</ref> Leeds qualified for the playoffs, however Roberts missed the final games of the season due to injury,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/leeds-united-handed-double-injury-2849659 |title=Leeds United handed double injury blow ahead of play-off clash with Derby County |date=9 May 2019 |publisher=Derbyshire Live}}</ref> including missing the semi-final playoffs matches versus sixth-placed [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]], as Leeds were beaten on 3\u20134 aggregate over the two legs. Despite taking a 1\u20130 win at Pride Park, to bring into a 1-0 aggregate lead into the home leg at Elland Road, Leeds lost 2\u20134 in an encounter that saw both teams reduced to 10 men and Derby progress to the final against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48196167 |title=Leeds United 2\u20134 Derby County (Derby win 4\u20133 on agg) |date=15 May 2019 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nRoberts ended up missing all the 2019\u201320 pre-season games and the start of the new season after undergoing knee surgery during May 2019.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/leeds-united-latest/leeds-united-s-tyler-roberts-misses-out-on-wales-squad-after-knee-operation-1-9793368 |title=Leeds United's Tyler Roberts misses out on Wales squad after knee operation |date=29 May 2019 |publisher=YEP}}</ref> He returned from injury against [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Chartlon Athletic]] on 28 September 2019, before scoring his first goal of the season against [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] in a 2\u20130 win on 2 November 2019,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/leeds-vs-qpr/409523 |title=Leeds United 2 QPR 0 |date=4 November 2019 |publisher=A=Sky Sports}}</ref> however Roberts picked up an injury against [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] on 26 November. He returned from injury as a substitute in Leeds' 4-5 win against [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] on 29 December 2019,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50882301 |title=Birmingham City 4-5 Leeds United: Bielsa's men beat Blues |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=4 January 2020}}</ref> but picked up a hamstring injury in the same game.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/latest-leeds-united-news/marcelo-bielsa-reveals-four-leeds-united-changes-arsenal-fa-cup-clash-and-issues-whites-injury-update-1355384 |title=Marcelo Bielsa reveals four Leeds United changes for Arsenal FA Cup clash and issues Whites injury update |date=4 January 2020 |website=Yorkshire Evening Post |language=English |access-date=4 January 2020}}</ref> The injury kept him out of the team until early February and, coming on as a 67th-minute substitute for striker [[Patrick Bamford]] on the 29th of that month, with Leeds two-nil ahead at [[Hull City F.C.|Hull]], Roberts put the game beyond doubt with the two final goals of the game within four minutes of each other \u2013 his first brace of the season and his second in a Leeds shirt.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51547861 |title=Hull 0-4 Leeds |date=29 February 2020 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Welsh national youth teams===\nThough he represented [[England national football team|England]], his country of birth, at schoolboy level, Roberts later elected to play for [[Wales national football team|Wales]] instead, qualifying for selection as two of his grandparents are Welsh.<ref name=\"BM\">{{Cite news |last=Stuart |first=Paul (5 January 2016) |url=http://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/tyler-roberts-lowdown-west-broms-10684923 |title=Tyler Roberts: The lowdown on West Brom's next great hope |work=Birmingham Mail |access-date=25 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, he captained the [[Wales national under-16 football team|Wales U16]] side to glory in the [[Victory Shield]], scoring in the final against [[Northern Ireland national under-16 football team|Northern Ireland]].<ref name=\"BBC1\" /> The result was Wales' first outright triumph in the competition since the 1948/49 edition.<ref name=\"FAW\">{{Cite news |url=http://contentfaw.aws-skybrid.co.uk/en/news/wales-beat-n-ireland-be-crowned-2014-victory-shield-champions/ |title=Wales beat N.Ireland to be Crowned 2014 Victory Shield Champions |date=21 November 2014 |access-date=16 May 2016 |website=Wales Football Association}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Jones |first=Dave  (21 November 2014) |url=http://www.dailypost.co.uk/sport/football/match-reports/victory-shield-northern-ireland-u16s-8147717 |title=Wales clinch title for the first time since 1948/49 |access-date=16 May 2016 |website=Daily Post}}</ref> Having trained with the senior side in between, he returned to the U16 side in November the following year and was part of the squad which retained the Victory Shield title.<ref name=\"SWA\">{{Cite news |last=Penman |first=Andrew (5 November 2015) |url=http://www.southwalesargus.co.uk/sport/13948019.Wales_under_16s_retain_Victory_Shield_in_Newport/ |title=Wales under-16s retain Victory Shield in Newport |access-date=17 May 2016 |website=South Wales Argus}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, following the conclusion of the League One season, he was included in [[Rob Page|Robert Page]]'s squad for the [[2017 Toulon Tournament]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39923634 |title=Toulon Tournament: Wales U20 without Liverpool's Ben Woodburn and Harry Wilson |date=16 May 2017 |website=BBC |access-date=18 May 2017}}</ref> After making his debut for the side in the tournament opener against [[Ivory Coast national under-20 football team|Ivory Coast]], Roberts made one further appearance, against [[France national under-20 football team|France]], as Wales were eliminated in the group stage.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.festival-foot-espoirs.com/direct_festival_foot_uk.php?tournoi_id=15 |title=Wales U20 2\u20132 Cote D'Ivoire |publisher=Foot Espoirs |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170601021623/http://www.festival-foot-espoirs.com/direct_festival_foot_uk.php?tournoi_id=15 |archive-date=1 June 2017 |access-date=16 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40100903 |title=Toulon Tournament: France U20 0-0 Wales U20 |date=30 May 2017 |work=BBC Sport |access-date=16 June 2017}}</ref> On 1 September, he made his debut for the [[Wales national under-21 football team|under-21]] side and scored the opening goal in a 3\u20130 victory over [[Switzerland national under-21 football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/09/01/europe/uefa-u21-championship/switzerland-under-21/wales-under-21/2429856/ |title=Switzerland U21 0\u20133 Wales U21 |publisher=Soccerway |access-date=1 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41131406 |title=Switzerland U21 0\u20133 Wales U21 |date=1 September 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=2 September 2017}}</ref> \n\n===Senior Wales national team===\nIn May 2015, Roberts, along with [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] winger [[Harry Wilson (footballer, born 1997)|Harry Wilson]], was called up by Wales manager [[Chris Coleman (footballer)|Chris Coleman]] to train with the senior squad.<ref name=\"WO\" /><ref name=\"BM\" /> In March 2017 he was named as a stand-by player for Wales' [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group D|World Cup qualifier]] against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39285564 |title=Tyler Roberts: West Brom forward commits international future to Wales |date=21 March 2017 |website=BBC |access-date=18 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe received his first full call-up in August 2018 when he was named in [[Ryan Giggs]]' squad for the nation's [[UEFA Nations League]] matches against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] and [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=O'Callaghan |first=Rory |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12018/11484779/paul-dummett-named-in-wales-squad-to-face-ireland-and-denmark |title=Paul Dummett named in Wales squad to face Ireland and Denmark |date=29 August 2018 |access-date=30 August 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> His debut followed against the former on 6 September, coming on as a second-half substitute for [[Gareth Bale]] in a 4\u20131 victory.<ref>{{Cite news |last=McCarthy |first=Ger |url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/sport/ireland-v-wales-moments-that-mattered-867325.html |title=Ireland v Wales \u2013 Moments that mattered |date=6 September 2018 |work=Irish Examiner |access-date=7 September 2018}}</ref> The following month, on 16 October 2018, Roberts was handed his first Wales start as the Republic of Ireland were again beaten 0\u20131 in [[Dublin]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.southwalesargus.co.uk/sport/16987289.ryan-giggs-wants-wales-to-win-nations-league-group/ |title=Ryan Giggs challenges Wales to finish the job against Denmark |website=South Wales Argus |access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 29 February 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<sup>1</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!League!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]\n|[[2015\u201316 West Bromwich Albion F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=\"15/16 appearances\">{{Soccerbase season|82907|2015|name=Tyler Roberts|access-date=15 May 2016}}</ref>\n|[[Premier League]]\n|1||0||