{"title_page": "Luis Muriel", "text_new": "{{good article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Luis Muriel\n| image       = FWC 2018 - Round of 16 - COL v ENG - Luis Muriel.jpg\n| caption     = Muriel with [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]\n| fullname    = Luis Fernando Muriel Fruto<ref name=\"FIFA\">{{cite web |url=https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia: List of players: Colombia |publisher=FIFA |format=PDF |page=5 |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=11 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619164139/https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF |archive-date=19 June 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1991|4|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Santo Tom\u00e1s, Atlantico|Santo Tom\u00e1s]], Colombia\n| height      = 1.79 m<ref>https://www.atalanta.it/personaggi/luis-muriel</ref>\n| position    = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Atalanta B.C|Atalanta]]\n| clubnumber  = 9\n| youthyears1 = 2001\u20132008\n| youthclubs1 = [[Junior de Barranquilla|Atl\u00e9tico Junior]]\n| youthyears2 = 2008\u20132009\n| youthclubs2 = [[Deportivo Cali]]\n| years1      = 2009\u20132010\n| clubs1      = [[Deportivo Cali]]\n| caps1       = 11\n| goals1      = 9\n| years2      = 2010\u20132015\n| clubs2      = [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]\n| caps2       = 57\n| goals2      = 15\n| years3      = 2010\u20132011\n| clubs3      = \u2192 [[Granada CF|Granada]] (loan)\n| caps3       = 7\n| goals3      = 0\n| years4      = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs4      = \u2192 [[U.S. Lecce|Lecce]] (loan)\n| caps4       = 29\n| goals4      = 7\n| years5      = 2015\n| clubs5      = \u2192 [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] (loan)\n| caps5       = 16\n| goals5      = 4\n| years6      = 2015\u20132017\n| clubs6      = [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]\n| caps6       = 63\n| goals6      = 17\n| years7      = 2017\u20132019\n| clubs7      = [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]]\n| caps7       = 35\n| goals7      = 8\n| years8      = 2019\n| clubs8      = \u2192 [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] (loan)\n| caps8       = 19\n| goals8      = 6\n| years9      = 2019\u2013\n| clubs9      = [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]]\n| caps9       = 22\n| goals9      = 13\n| nationalyears1 = 2011\n| nationalteam1  = [[Colombia national under-20 football team|Colombia U20]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 4\n| nationalyears2 = 2012\u2013\n| nationalteam2  = [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 32\n| nationalgoals2 = 5\n| pcupdate = 16:32, 1 March 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = 15 November 2019\n}}\n{{Spanish name|Muriel|Fruto}}\n'''Luis Fernando Muriel Fruto''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8lwiz mu\u02c8\u027ejel}};{{efn|In isolation, ''Luis'' is pronounced {{IPA-es|lwis|}}.}} born 16 April 1991) is a Colombian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]] for Italian club [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombian national team]].\n\nHaving started his professional career with Colombian side [[Deportivo Cali]], Muriel joined [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]. His first two seasons at the club saw him [[Loan (sports)|loaned]] out to [[Granada CF|Granada]] and [[U.S. Lecce|Lecce]] respectively before returning to the club in 2012, during which year he won the [[Gran Gal\u00e0 del Calcio#Serie A Best Young Revelation|Serie A Best Young Revelation]] award alongside [[Stephan El Shaarawy]]. After scoring 15 league goals in 57 appearances, Muriel joined fellow [[Serie A]] side Sampdoria in January 2015. He spent two-and-a-half seasons with the club, scoring 21 goals in 79 league appearances before joining Sevilla in 2017. In January 2019, he was sent back to Italy on loan with Fiorentina. In June 2019, Muriel signed for [[Serie A]] side Atalanta for a reported \u20ac18m.\n\nMuriel is currently a [[Colombia national football team|Colombian international]] having represented his nation at a full international level since 2012. He made his senior debut in June 2012, in a [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifying]] match against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] and scored his first goal the following year, netting against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]]. He later took part at the [[2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2015]] and [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2019]] editions of the [[Copa Am\u00e9rica]], and the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Deportivo Cali===\nHaving spent his formative years with [[Atl\u00e9tico Junior]], Muriel joined Colombian [[Categor\u00eda Primera A|Primera A]] side [[Deportivo Cali]] in January 2009.<ref name=\"scouting report\">{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/scouting-report-introducing-chelsea-target-luis-muriel-28575|title=Scouting Report: Introducing Chelsea target Luis Muriel|website=Calcio Mercato|last=Mitchell|first=Steve|date=30 November 2016|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>[http://www.canalrcn.com/futbolmania/index.php?op=desarrollo&idS=1539&idC=102498 Futbolman\u00eda RCN (ed.): \u00abTres goles de Muriel le dan respiro al Deportivo Cali \u00bb] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307190357/http://www.canalrcn.com/futbolmania/index.php?idc=102498&ids=1539&op=desarrollo |date=7 March 2016 }}. Canalrcn.com.</ref> He made his debut against [[Envigado FC]] on 12 July 2009 in what would be his only appearance for the year before scoring nine goals in 10 appearances the following season. Muriel's early form for Deportivo, which included a [[hat-trick]] against [[Once Caldas]] in his third match, earned him the nickname \"the Colombian Ronaldo\", in comparison to former [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] striker [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], and midway through the season he was signed by Italian Serie A side Udinese.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://elheraldoslp.com.mx/2017/06/16/barcelona-tiene-a-muriel-en-su-radar/|title=Barcelona tiene a Muriel en su radar|website=El Heraldo|date=16 June 2017|accessdate=9 July 2017|language=es}}</ref><ref name=Goal>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/2892/transfer-zone/2013/05/30/4014129/the-colombian-ronaldo-introducing-liverpool-target-luis|title='The Colombian Ronaldo' - Introducing Liverpool target Luis Muriel|website=Goal|last=Doyle|first=Mark|date=30 May 2013|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://espndeportes.espn.com/noticias/nota?s=ita&id=1019622&type=story|title=Luis Muriel jugar\u00e1 en Udinese|website=ESPN|date=13 May 2010|accessdate=9 July 2017|language=es}}</ref>\n\n===Udinese===\n[[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] officially completed the signing of Muriel on 30 May 2010 for a reported fee of \u20ac1.5m.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/why-man-utd-and-liverpool-have-joined-battle-luis-muriel-new-ronaldo-3090141#.UTquphy0KSo|title=Why Man Utd and Liverpool have joined the battle for Luis Muriel - the new Ronaldo|website=Tribal Football|last=Beattie|first=Chris|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> In terms of the [[Transfer (association football)|transfer]] agreement, Udinese obtained 70% of Muriel's playing rights with the remaining 30% being retained by Deportivo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardia.com/historico/61968-luis-muriel-pasa-del-cali-al-udinese-italiano|title=Luis Muriel pasa del Cali al Udinese italiano|website=Vanguardia|date=14 May 2010|accessdate=9 July 2017|language=es}}</ref> Shortly after his arrival in [[Udine]], however, he was [[Loan (sports)|loaned]] to [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] side [[Granada CF|Granada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/2010/07/12/futbol/equipos/granada/1278952580.html|title=El Granada ficha a los jugadores del Udinese Muriel y Siqueira|website=Marca|date=12 July 2010|accessdate=12 November 2017|language=es}}</ref>\n\n====Loans to Granada & Lecce====\nMuriel completed his loan move to Granada on 12 July 2010.<ref>[http://www.granadacf.es/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=777&catid=777 Granada Club de F\u00fatbol \u2013 Web oficial]. Granada CF. (in Spanish)</ref> The club achieved promotion to [[La Liga]] for the first time in 35 years but it was an unsuccessful spell for Muriel, as he made only seven appearances for the season and failed to score.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12040/6995921/granada-promoted-to-la-liga|title=Granada promoted to La Liga|website=Sky Sports|date=18 June 2011|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-espana.net/64657/atleti-interest-muriel|title=Atleti interest in Muriel|website=Football Espana|date=19 June 2017|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nUpon the expiration of his loan with Granada, Muriel was loaned out again for the following season to fellow Serie A side, [[U.S. Lecce|Lecce]]. He made his debut for the club on 27 October 2011, coming on as a second-half [[substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Daniele Corvia]] in a 2\u20130 loss to [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2011/10/27/italy/serie-a/us-citta-di-palermo/us-lecce/1175709/|title=Palermo v Lecce: 2\u20130|website=Soccerway|date=27 October 2017|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> On his first start for the club the following month, against [[A.C. Cesena|Cesena]], Muriel was [[Fouls and misconduct (association football)|sent off]] for two bookable offences. Lecce hung on to claim a 1\u20130 victory, however, thanks to a goal from fellow countryman and Udinese-loanee, [[Juan Cuadrado]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/liga_italiana/epoca-1112/jogos/6590|website=Sapo Desporto|title=Cesena 0\u20131 Lecce|date=6 November 2011|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> He improved to end the campaign with a return of seven goals in 29 appearances, though his efforts were not enough to prevent Lecce from being relegated to [[Serie B]].<ref name=Goal/> His form during the course of the season garnered the attention of [[A.C. Milan]] and [[Internazionale]], with both clubs making official offers to sign him, but Muriel confirmed that he would be returning to Udinese.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/11/transfer-zone/2012/04/10/3025932/inter-ac-milan-have-made-official-offers-for-me-says-luis|title=Inter & AC Milan have made official offers for me, says Luis Muriel|website=Goal|last=Coerts|first=Stefen|date=10 April 2012|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Return to Udinese====\nMuriel's poor physical condition upon his return to Udinese drew the ire of [[Francesco Guidolin]], with the club [[manager (association football)|manager]] insisting that he needed to lose {{convert|5|lbs|kg}}, despite the player scoring four goals against Arta Cedarchis in a pre-season [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]].<ref name=Goal/><ref name=ES>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurosport.com/football/meet-udineses-luis-muriel-the-forward-aiming-to-emulate-brazils-ronaldo_sto4716625/story.shtml|title=Meet Udinese\u2019s Luis Muriel, the forward aiming to emulate Brazil\u2019s Ronaldo|website=Eurosport|date=12 June 2013|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> He was able to get in shape for the start of the season and made his debut in a 2\u20131 defeat against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] on 25 August 2012, providing the assist to [[Maicosuel]] for the opening goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/22104|title=Fiorentina 2 - 1 Udinese|website=Football Italia|date=25 August 2012|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> He signed a contract extension the following month, signing an improved five-year deal with the club.<ref name=SK>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/luis-muriel-colombias-fallen-star-taking-serie-a-storm-sampdoria|title=Luis Muriel: Colombia's fallen star now taking Serie A by storm with Sampdoria|website=Sportskeeda|last=De Cosemo|first=Harry|date=16 March 2017|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> In January 2012, Muriel was awarded the [[Gran Gal\u00e0 del Calcio#Serie A Best Young Revelation|Serie A Best Young Revelation]] award alongside Milan's [[Stephan El Shaarawy]] in recognition of his form with Lecce and Udinese the previous year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://forzaitalianfootball.com/2013/01/gran-gala-del-calcio-2012-winners/|title=Gran Gala Del Calcio 2012 \u2013 Winners|website=Forza Italian Football|date=28 January 2013|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> By the conclusion of the season, he had contributed a return of 11 goals in 22 Serie A appearances, despite having missed nearly four months of football because of a hairline fracture of his left femur.<ref name=Goal/><ref name=ES/>\n\nThe following season, in the qualifying playoff rounds of the [[2013\u201314 UEFA Europa League]], Muriel scored his first ever European goals, netting twice in a 3\u20131 victory over [[\u0160iroki Brijeg]] and in his first league match of the season, scored against reigning [[Coppa Italia]] champions, [[Lazio]] in a 2\u20131 loss.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/siroki-bjeg-vs-udinese/299075|title=Football Results Thursday 1st August 2013|website=Sky Sports|date=1 August 2013|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://forzaitalianfootball.com/2013/08/lazio-2-1-udinese-muriel-strike-not-enough-as-biancocelesti-win/|title=Lazio 2-1 Udinese: Muriel Strike Not Enough As Biancocelesti Win|website=Forza Italian Football|date=25 August 2013|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> His form declined however, as he struggled with weight and injury issues, and over the course of the next season-and-a-half he scored only four goals in 35 league appearances, including a spell without any goals in 11 matches from the start of the [[2014\u201315 Serie A|2014\u201315 Serie A season]].<ref name=SK/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2326745-luis-muriel-colombian-ronaldo-high-risk-high-reward-for-sampdoria|title=Luis Muriel: Colombian Ronaldo High Risk, High Reward for Sampdoria|website=Bleacher Report|last=Jiang|first=Allan|date=12 January 2015|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> He ultimately amassed 15 goals in 57 appearances for the club, before leaving to join [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] in 2015.<ref name=FFT>{{cite web|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/sampdoria-land-udinese-duo-muriel-and-coda|title=Sampdoria Land Udinese Duo Muriel and Cora|website=Four Four Two|date=22 January 2015|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Sampdoria===\nIn spite of his struggles with Udinese, Sampdoria completed the double loan signings of Muriel and teammate [[Andrea Coda]] on 22 January 2015, with an obligation to purchase both players at the end of the season for a combined sum of \u20ac12m. In terms of the agreement, Muriel signed a contract with Sampdoria until 30 June 2019.<ref name=SK/><ref>{{cite web|url=\nhttp://www.sampdoria.it/finalmente-blucerchiati-muriel-e-coda-benvenuti-al-doria/|title=Finalmente Blucerchiati: Murie e Coda, Benvenuti al Doria|publisher=UC Sampdoria|date=22 January 2015|accessdate=9 July 2017|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://gianlucadimarzio.com/it/sampdoria-e-fatta-per-muriel-dalludinese-arriva-anche-coda-i-dettagli|title=\nSampdoria, \u00e8 fatta per Muriel: dall\u2019Udinese arriva anche Coda, i dettagli|date=9 January 2015|access-date=11 July 2017|website=GianlucaDiMarzio.com|language=Italian}}</ref> He scored four times in 16 appearances during his loan spell before completing a permanent transfer at the end of the season.<ref name=SK/> In his final campaign with the club he recorded a career best return of 11 league goals and five [[Assist (football)|assists]], which prompted [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] to break their club record to sign him at the end of the season.<ref name=beIN>{{cite web|url=http://www.beinsports.com/au/football/news/sevilla-strikes-deal-for-luis-muriel/589702|title=Sevilla strikes deal for Luis Muriel|website=beIN Sports|date=8 July 2017|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Sevilla===\nOn 11 July 2017, La Liga side [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] announced the signing of Muriel for a reported club-record fee \u20ac20m, with potential add-ons.<ref name=beIN/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sevillafc.es/actualidad/noticias/el-fichaje-de-muriel-ya-es-oficial|title=El Fichaje de Muriel ya es Oficial|website=Sevilla|date=11 July 2017|accessdate=11 July 2017}}</ref> He made his debut on 19 August, starting in a 1\u20131 draw with [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] and scored his first goal for the club on 17 September, netting the winner in a 1\u20130 victory over [[Girona FC|Girona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vavel.com/es/futbol/sevilla-fc/818862-luis-muriel-no-estuve-afortunado-de-cara-al-gol.html|title=Luis Muriel: \"No estuve afortunado de cara al gol\"|website=Vavel|last=Carral|first=Gorka|date=20 August 2017|accessdate=20 August 2017|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kwese.espn.com/football/spanish-primera-division/story/3206568/la-liga-real-madrid-get-needed-win-vs-la-real-sevilla-beat-girona-to-go-second|title=Real Madrid get needed win vs. La Real; Sevilla beat Girona to go second|website=ESPN|date=17 September 2017|accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref>\nFollowing a disappointing debut campaign, in which he only scored 9 goals in 46 appearances, Muriel found himself behind [[Wissam Ben Yedder]] and new club signings [[Andr\u00e9 Silva (footballer, born 1995)|Andr\u00e9 Silva]] and [[Quincy Promes]] in the [[pecking order]] for Sevilla the following season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.diariodesevilla.es/sevillafc/mercado-depreciacion-gol-error_0_1280872493.html|title=Volver a la 'pole', el nuevo reto de Muriel|publisher=Diario de Sevilla|last=Alba|first=Jesus|date=11 September 2018|accessdate=12 September 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to Fiorentina====\nOn 2 January 2019, Muriel returned to Serie A after signing with [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] on loan for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/news/fiorentina-beat-ac-milan-to-loan-signing-of-sevillas-muriel/heok0xsstohe10bokuxh8d5im|title=Fiorentina beat AC Milan to loan signing of Sevilla's Muriel|publisher=Goal|last=Benson|first=Ryan|date=1 January 2019|accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref> He scored a hat-trick on his non-competitive debut a week later in a win over Maltese side, [[Hibernians F.C.|Hibernians]] before making his official debut on 14 January in a 2\u20130 Coppa Italia win over [[Torino F.C.|Torino]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.football-italia.net/133041/muriel-hat-trick-viola-debut|title=Muriel hat-trick on Viola debut|publisher=Football Italia|date=9 January 2019|accessdate=16 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://deportes.canalrcn.com/futbol/futbol-internacional/con-debut-oficial-de-luis-muriel-fiorentina-clasifica-cuartos-de-la-copa|title=Con debut oficial de Luis Muriel, Fiorentina clasifica a cuartos de la Copa Italia|publisher=Deportes|language=Spanish|date=14 January 2019|accessdate=16 January 2019}}</ref> He then scored twice on his league debut on 20 January during a 3\u20133 draw with former club, Sampdoria.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.squawka.com/en/news/luis-muriel-reminds-fiorentina-boss-of-ronaldo-the-phenomenon/1078179#HAMeeVxMx8O0LaFm.97|title=Luis Muriel reminds Fiorentina boss of \u2018Ronaldo the Phenomenon\u2019|publisher=Squawka|last=Green|first=Ben|date=21 January 2019|accessdate=28 January 2019}}</ref> He ultimately scored six league goals during his loan spell but was not signed permanently after the club underwent a change in ownership.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.francefootball.fr/news/Transferts-luis-muriel-seville-a-l-atalanta-officiel/1032300|title=Transferts : Luis Muriel (S\u00e9ville) \u00e0 l'Atalanta (officiel)|publisher=France Football|language=French|date=21 June 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2019/06/09/5cfd15caca474132468b460c.html|title=Muriel has plenty of admirers in Italy|publisher=Marca|last=Guevara|first=Rocio|date=9 June 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Atalanta===\nOn 21 June 2019, after a successful loan spell with Fiorentina, Muriel returned to Serie A after signing with [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] in a permanent deal worth a reported \u20ac18m.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://football-espana.net/78828/atalanta-sign-sevilla-striker-luis-muriel|title=Atalanta sign Sevilla striker Luis Muriel|publisher=Football Espana|last=Staff|first=Football Espana|date=21 June 2019|accessdate=21 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Youth team===\nMuriel represented Colombia at [[Colombia national under-20 football team|U20 level]] and featured for the nation at the [[2011 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] for which Colombia were the host nation. On 6 August 2011, having previously scored twice against [[France national under-20 football team|France]], he scored the only goal of the match as Colombia defeated [[South Korea national under-20 football team|Korea Republic]] 1\u20130 to progress from the group stages with a perfect record.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=255641/match=300145852/match-report.html|title=Colombians finish perfect, South Koreans through|website=FIFA|date=6 August 2011|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> Muriel ultimately scored four goals for the tournament before Colombia were knocked out by [[Mexico national under-20 football team|Mexico]] in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/archive/colombia2011/statistics/players/goal-scored.html|title=FIFA U-20 World Cup Colombia 2011|website=FIFA|accessdate=12 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Senior team===\n[[File:FWC 2018 - Round of 16 - COL v ENG - Photo 109.jpg|thumb|Muriel stepping up to take a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]] during [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]]'s [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] defeat to [[England national football team|England]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].]]\nMuriel was called up to the [[Colombia national football team|senior side]] for the first time in 2012 by new manager [[Jos\u00e9 P\u00e9kerman]] and made his debut in a 1\u20130 [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification|World Cup qualifier]] loss to [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] on 10 June. He scored his first goal the following year, scoring in a friendly against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]] on 6 February 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1701/colombia/2012/05/16/3107186/muriel-included-in-colombia-squad-for-world-cup-qualifiers|title=Muriel included in Colombia squad for World Cup qualifiers|website=Goal|last=Edwards|first=Daniel|date=16 May 2012|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/scout-report-luis-muriel|title=Scout report - Luis Muriel|website=Sportskeeda|date=4 May 2014|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> The following year, he was one of seven players cut from Colombia's extended squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kwese.espn.com/football/club/name/208/blog/post/1860231/headline|title=Life after Falcao for Colombia|website=ESPN|last=Worswick|first=Carl|date=4 June 2014|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> He was a member of Colombia's squad for the [[2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica]] but was overlooked for the [[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario]] the following year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elheraldo.co/rincon-juniorista/el-regalo-de-luis-fernando-muriel-para-ovelar-264647|title=El regalo de Luis Fernando Muriel para Ovelar|website=El Heraldo|last=Juniorista|first=Rincon|date=5 June 2016|accessdate=10 July 2017|language=es}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018 he was named in Colombia's preliminary 35 man [[Colombia national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 Squad|publisher=Goal|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref> He featured sporadically as Colombia reached the Round of 16 where they were eliminated following a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] defeat to [[England national football team|England]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/07/03/england-vs-colombia-world-cup-2018-live-score-harry-kane-latest/|title=England banish penalty curse to pass Colombia test and reach World Cup quarter-final|publisher=The Telegraph|last1=Wallace|last2=Tylers|first1=Sam|first2=Alan|date=4 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe following summer, Muriel was included in the 23-man Colombia squad for the [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://copaamerica.com/en/teams/colombia/ |title=Colombia |publisher=Copa Am\u00e9rica |accessdate=4 October 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==Style of play== \nIn his youth, Muriel was often praised in the media for his precocious performances during his early career in Italy,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fcinter1908.it/in-evidenza/cesarini-inter-su-muriel-tutti-i-top-club-hanno-riconosciuto-il-talento-l-udinese/ |title=Cesarini: \u201cInter su Muriel? Tutti i top club hanno riconosciuto il talento. L\u2019Udinese\u2026\u201d |publisher=F.C. Inter 1908 |last1=Vitiello |first1=Daniele |language=Italian |date=17 April 2012 |accessdate=4 February 2019 }}</ref> which led him to win the Serie A Best Young Revelation Award in 2012.<ref name=\"ran Gal\u00e0 del Calcio Aic\"/> Several footballing figures in Italy, such as manager [[Massimiliano Allegri]], have recognised Muriel for his speed and technique on the ball, as well as the potential which he already demonstrated as a youngster;<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Milan/10-03-2012/allegri-mai-problemi-ibra-stessa-voglia-vincere-81581927627.shtml |title=Allegri: \"Mai problemi con Ibra Stessa voglia di vincere\" |work=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |date=10 March 2012 |accessdate=4 February 2019 }}</ref> his former Udinese teammate [[Antonio Di Natale]] even compared him to [[Alexis S\u00e1nchez]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/33750/muriel-will-be-great-says-di-natale|title=Muriel will be a great, says Di Natale|publisher=Football Italia|date=2 May 2013}}</ref> Although Muriel is usually deployed as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|centre-forward]], he is a versatile [[Forward (association football)|forward]], who is capable of playing in several offensive positions; indeed, during the 2012\u201313 season, under his former Udinese manager Francesco Guidolin, he also demonstrated his creative capabilities in a more withdrawn, central role behind another striker, which frequently saw him operate as either a [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|second striker]] or [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]].<ref name=\"fenomeno\"/> He is also capable of playing as a [[Forward (association football)#Winger|winger]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Milan/30-12-2018/mercato-muriel-milan-salta-accordo-colombiano-sceglie-fiorentina-3101673299904.shtml |title=Mercato, Muriel verso la Fiorentina |publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |date=30 December 2018 |accessdate=25 April 2019 }}</ref> A fast, talented, creative, two-footed, and technically gifted [[Striker (association football)|striker]], with good [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills, pace, agility, acceleration, and an eye for goal, Muriel's playing style, physical build, and appearance have led him to be compared to former Brazil striker Ronaldo.<ref name=\"scouting report\"/><ref name=ES/><ref name=\"fenomeno\">{{cite web |url=https://www.calcionews24.com/muriel-e-un-fenomeno-ora-con-di-natale-poi-c-e-radamel-291929 |title=Muriel \u00e8 un fenomeno: ora con Di Natale, poi c?\u00e8 Radamel |publisher=www.calcionews24.com |language=Italian |date=9 January 2013 |accessdate=4 February 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"cavallo\">{{cite news |url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2015/03/18/muriel-il-cavallo-selvaggio-che-adesso-fa-sognareGenova17.html |title=Muriel, il cavallo selvaggio che adesso fa sognare |work=La Repubblica |language=Italian |last=Mangini |first=Lorenzo |date=18 March 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2019 }}</ref> Muriel has stated that this comparison is likely due to the fact that, as a youngster, he was an admirer of Ronaldo during the latter's time with [[Inter Milan]].<ref name=Goal/> Muriel went on to say that he supported Inter Milan because Ronaldo was playing for them at the time, and that he was initially a Milan fan.<ref name=\"mercato\">{{cite web |url=https://www.calciomercato.it/news/83417/mercato_udinese_muriel_da_piccolo_tifavo_milan_ma |title=Mercato Udinese, Muriel: \"Da piccolo tifavo Milan, ma...\" |publisher=www.calciomercato.it |language=Italian |date=2 February 2013 |accessdate=4 February 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://football-italia.net/35100/muriel-im-inter-fan|title=Muriel: 'I'm an Inter fan'|publisher=Football Italia|date=8 June 2013}}</ref> Coincidentally, Muriel also stated that, like his childhood idol, he also suffers from weight issues, and even had to lose five kg at one point during the 2012\u201313 season.<ref name=ES/><ref name=\"mercato\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2013/08/08/who-is-manchester-united-target-luis-muriel-3916602/|title=Who is: Manchester United target Luis Muriel|publisher=metro.co.uk|last=Griffiths|first=Danny|date=8 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.calcionews24.com/udinese-guidolin-muriel-deve-perdere-peso-252532 |title=Udinese, Guidolin: \u201cMuriel deve perdere peso\u201d |publisher=www.calcionews24.com |language=Italian |date=20 July 2012 |accessdate=4 February 2019 }}</ref> This meant that he had to be consistent with his fitness regime, which enabled him to achieve a similar level of athletic ability to Ronaldo.<ref name=Goal/><ref>[http://www.whoscored.com/Blog/1krrumhjpuwwhqeggati9a/Show/Player-Focus-Luis-Muriel-The-Forgotten-Forward-in-This-Summers-Transfer-Window Player Focus: Luis Muriel \u2013 The Forgotten Forward in This Summer's Transfer Window]. Whoscored.com (18 July 2013).</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/10/italy/2012/07/20/3254214/guidolin-muriel-must-lose-weight|title=Guidolin: Muriel must lose weight|publisher=Goal.com|last=Patient|first=Doug|date=20 July 2012}}</ref> Aside from Ronaldo, another one of Muriel's major influences as a footballer in his youth was compatriot [[Iv\u00e1n Valenciano]].<ref name=\"cavallo\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 1 March 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/luis-fernando-muriel-fruto/83929/|title=Luis Fernando Muriel Fruto|website=Soccerway|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club!!rowspan=\"2\"|Season!!colspan=\"3\"|League!!colspan=\"2\"|Cup<sup>1</sup>!!colspan=\"2\"|Continental<sup>2</sup>!!colspan=\"2\"|Other!!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!League!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Deportivo Cali]]||2009||[[Categor\u00eda Primera A|Primera A]]\n||1||0||rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"6\"|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|2010|||Primera A||10||9||10||9\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!11!!9!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!11!!9\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]||[[2010\u201311 Serie A|2010\u201311]]||[[Serie A]]\n|0||0||0||0||colspan=\"4\"|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Serie A|2012\u201313]]\n|Serie A\n|22||11||1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"